article.headline: Belmont 99, East Tenn. St. 78
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Belmont got 41 points from a pair of guards to overpower ETSU 99-78 Sunday in an Atlantic Sun Conference showdown. Belmont (17-10, 15-5) got a game-high 21 points from Josh Goodwin, and 20 from Brian Collins to lead five Bruins finishing in double figures. Boomer Herndon scored 16, Justin Hare 12 and Andrew Preston 10 for Belmont. ETSU (15-12, 12-8) was led by Tim Smith and Courtney Pigram with 18 points apiece. Travis Strong and Eryk Thomas scored 11 each for the Bucs. Belmont used a strong second half to put the game away after leading 46-40 at the half. Belmont finished in second place in the regular season conference standings, while ETSU finished fifth. No. 2 seed Belmont is slated to face No. 7 seed Campbell in the first round of the conference tournament. No. 5 see ETSU will face No. 4 Gardner-Webb in the first round. The Atlantic Sun tournament begins Thursday at ETSU.
